<TITLE> Belgium and Netherlands submit bid to co-host World Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BRUSSELS, Jan 31 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The Dutch and Belgian football associations have submitted their bid to FIFA to co-host the World Cup finals in 2018 or 2022, a spokesman for the bid said on Friday. "We have sent a letter to FIFA indicating our wish to host the tournament which should reach them by Monday's deadline," the spokesman said. Soccer's world governing body FIFA said it already had six proposals on the tablefrom Indonesia, England, Japan, Qatar, Russia and a joint application from Spain and Portugal. The United States said it would formally submit its bid to FIFA on Monday and several other associations have indicated that they will join the process. The 2010 World Cup will be held in South Africa while Brazil will host the 2014 tournament. FIFA is due to announce the hosts of both the 2018 and 2022 tournaments in December 2010. Belgium and Netherlands co-hosted the 2000 European Championship
